<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Race vs. Race</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Ice">Ice</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 6:07 p.m. 7/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Race vs. Race<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2034" TARGET=_self>Re: Race vs. Race</A> (Stupid)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Personally, I detest this. I feel that Verant has provided an

<BR>&gt; excellent role playing environment with a set "role"
<BR>&gt; for evey player. In my opinion, the racial/alignment guidlines
<BR>&gt; were set up for a reason and they should be adhered to. Yes,
<BR>&gt; Dark Elves have no Druids or Bards. That's a limitation. But on
<BR>&gt; the other hand, Dark Elves have Ultravision - almost perfect
<BR>&gt; night vision - no other race has this. That's an advantage. It
<BR>&gt; all works out.
<P>&gt; My feeling is that each race was designed to be more-or-less
<BR>&gt; balanced in the "big picture". Between Dark Elves,
<BR>&gt; Trolls and Ogres, (so-called) "evil" races have access
<BR>&gt; to every possible skill and spell in the game. Why would you
<BR>&gt; need (or even WANT) to group with (so-called) "good"
<BR>&gt; races and classes?
<P>&gt; I guess, deep down, I'm a role player. But I'm the minority.
<BR>&gt; Most people, it seems, are unwilling (or unable) to accept the
<BR>&gt; limitations that the game implies. But while I dislike it, I
<BR>&gt; also know that there is very little that I can do to change it.
<P>Im not disagreeing with you at all, and i think you are right, all i am saying is the way it is now, without haveint to take big faction hits for killing your own race, you will not see this good vs. evil thing as big as you might like. Thats just how i feel. Maybe if they made it to were if you killed so many of your own kind you were Kos by your citys guards things would be different, but as the way it stands i just dont see it :(
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
